character.name: Floyd Waters
character.description: Floyd is a head taller than other Orks, but is misidentified as a small Troll.
character.concept: Melee Tank. Make sure the mage isn't geeked

contact.name: Ed "Blackwing" Jackson
contact.notes:
Ed Jackson, AKA "Blackwing", is a NANophile (someone who fetishizes the members of the Native American Nations and their culture). As a black American, he was the first "blacksmith" that Floyd found while he was looking for an armorer to start his runner career. This misconception led to a night of drunken fun at a nearby club that Floyd moonlit at for a time.

Ed's shop is demarkated with a wood-burned symbol of Hermes's winged shoe on a metal, riveted backing. This earned him the tongue-in-cheek alias of "Blackwing".

contact.name: Martin "Maw" D'Amagio
contact.notes:
A loan shark that Floyd used to work for. He has metal teeth that are all sharpened to a point to make him look like an actual shark. Intimidating, right? How does he even eat food?

Martin owns the shell company TPA, which owns Triddies where Floyd is now part-timing

contact.name: Felicia "Cherry Doll" Etsitty
contact.notes:
Called "Maraschino" behind her back by the older employees because of her reddened skin

Felicia is a new stipper at "Triddies", where Floyd works part time at night as a security guard when the trids are being shipped. Felicia and Floyd have met each other in passing, usually after Felicia has put in a solid 3 hour recording session. Floyd thinks she's "pretty enough to be in the big time movies"

"Triddies" is a sub-trid-iary of TPA (Trid Pornography of America). TPA is a shell company that is operated in the shadows by Martin D'Amagio of "Anytime Loans"
